                                    "type": "marked",
                                    "content": {
                                        "content": "### First things first \n\n+ All claims must be reported to the insurer as soon as possible after discovering the loss or other incident. \n+ If your phone has been lost or stolen, you must contact your network provider as soon as reasonably possible. \n+ If your phone is stolen, you should inform the police and get a crime reference number as soon as reasonably possible.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n### If you're outside the UK at the time of discovering the incident\n\nYou must:\n\n+ Contact your network provider as soon as reasonably possible after discovering the loss or theft.\n+ Register your claim as soon as possible. \n\nIf your phone is stolen, you should inform the police and get a crime reference number as soon as reasonably possible. Please note we won't repair or replace your device until you return to the UK.\n\n### How to make a claim"
